description: Attested since 1865-70. From New Latin. The first element is from Ancient Greek ἄρκτος (árktos) (see Arctic), the second from γαῖᾰ (gaîa, “land, earth”).

entries.meaning: (biogeography) Of or relating to the Arctogea, a biogeographical division comprising the Holarctic and Paleotropical regions.
